orted}}\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = [[Ghaziabad]]\n| arrival_date    = 5 March 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=05|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 182<ref name=mohfw/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 17<ref name=mohfw/>\n| deaths          = 2<ref name=mohfw/>\n| territories     = 24\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = https://www.mohfw.gov.in/\n| youtube         = \n}}\nThe [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]] was first confirmed in the Indian state of [[Uttar Pradesh]] on 5 March 2020, with first positive case in [[Ghaziabad]]. As of 3 April 2020, the state has 182 confirmed cases.<ref name=mohfw>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mohfw.gov.in/|title=Home &#124; Ministry of Health and Family Welfare &#124; GOI|website=www.mohfw.gov.in}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n\n'''March'''\n\n* '''''5 March''''' - A middle-aged man in [[Ghaziabad]] who had travel history with [[Iran]] tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-update-new-case-reported-from-ghaziabad-india-now-has-30-patients-11583401881606.html|title=Coronavirus update: New case reported from Ghaziabad, India now has 30 patients|date=5 March 2020|website=Livemint}}</ref>\n* '''''9 March''''' - A factory worker was tested positive after he came in contact with the coronavirus positive businessman from [[Agra]]. Earlier, five members from the businessman's family were tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-update-two-new-cases-from-kerala-agra-take-total-number-to-41-11583727824797.html|title=Coronavirus update: 4 new cases reported, India now has 43 COVID-19 patients|date=9 March 2020|website=Livemint}}</ref>\n* '''''12 March''''' - A tourist guide in [[Noida]], who came in contact with [[Italian people|Italian]] guests was tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/one-more-tests-covid-19-positive-uttar-pradesh-tally-is-nine/articleshow/74586351.cms|title=One more tests positive for Covid-19; Uttar Pradesh tally is nine &#124; Lucknow News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> Also a woman doctor from [[Canada]] tested positive in state capital [[Lucknow]], taking the total cases in the state to ten.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/woman-doctor-from-canada-tests-coronavirus-positive-in-lucknow-54338|title=Woman doctor from Canada tests coronavirus positive in Lucknow|first=Tribune News|last=Service|website=Tribuneindia News Service}}</ref>\n* '''''13 March''''' - An employee of a private firm in Noida tested positive who had travelled to Italy and [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/delhi/coronavirus-noida-employee-with-travel-history-to-italy-tests-positive-6312385/|title=At Noida firm, 707 workers in contact with coronavirus patient quarantined|date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Five patients were recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/7-more-patients-in-india-cured-of-covid-19/story-KdGoZb0ufeippFwgfz7N2O.html|title=Coronavirus: India fights back, 7 more patients cured of Covid-19|date=14 March 2020|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n* '''''15 March''''' - State's twelfth case was reported in Lucknow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-one-more-covid19-case-reported-in-lucknow-uttar-pradesh-1655527-2020-03-14|title=Coronavirus in India: One more Covid-19 case reported in Lucknow|first1=Shivendra Srivastava|last1=LucknowMarch 14|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=March 14|first3=2020 16:32|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref>\n* '''''17 March''''' - Two people who returned from [[France]] tested positive in Noida<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-news-live-updates-india-delhi-italy-china-death-toll-confirmed-cases-europe-1656253-2020-03-17|title=Coronavirus: Govt restricts travel of Indian passport holders with immediate effect|date=17 March 2020|website=India Today}}</ref>\n* '''''18 March''''' - A man from Gautam Buddha Nagar district in Noida who had returned from [[Indonesia]] tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/world/coronavirus-live-updates-covid-19-pandemic-maharashtra-delhi-pune-mumbai-karnataka-kerala-bengal-death-toll-5044481.html|title=Coronavirus Highlights: PM Modi to address nation tomorrow|website=Moneycontrol}}</ref>\n* '''''19 March''''' - Two more people in state, one from Lucknow and the other from [[Lakhimpur Kheri district]], tested positive. Later, an [[HCL Technologies|HCL]] employee in Noida who had returned from international travel tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-live-updates-total-number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-india-rises-march-19-2020/liveblog/74701641.cms|title=Coronavirus Updates: France reports 108 new coronavirus deaths in last 24 hours|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/hcl-employee-in-noida-tests-positive-for-covid-19-cases-in-up-reach-17/story-ohYtiJ2wKalLqgU86aNHYO.html|title=HCL employee in Noida tests positive for Covid-19, cases in UP reach 19|date=19 March 2020|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n* '''''20 March''''' - [[Bollywood]] singer [[Kanika Kapoor]] who returned from [[London]] tested positive in Lucknow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/baby-doll-singer-kanika-kapoor-tests-coronavirus-positive-she-hid-travel-history-threw-party-at-5-star-1657811-2020-03-20|title=Baby Doll singer Kanika Kapoor tests coronavirus positive. She hid travel history, partied at 5-star|first1=India Today Web Desk New|last1=DelhiMarch 20|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=March 20|first3=2020 20:11|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref> Four more people tested positive in Lucknow - three related to a previously-infected doctor and one with a travel history to [[Gulf]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-highlights-covid-19-india-noida-mumbai-bangalore-cases-count-alert-novel-latest-news-today-bird-flu-virus-2-8165681.html|title=Coronavirus outbreak Updates: Italy records highest COVID-19 toll in one day with 627 deaths; 'you are not invincible', WHO tells youth|website=Firstpost}}</ref>\n*'''21 ''March''''' - [[Noida]] confirmed a case in Supertech CapeTown society.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/noida-coronavirus-supertech-cape-town-society-in-lockdown-covid19-case-600131|title=Noida society in lockdown after person tests COVID-19 positive|last=|first=|date=|website=India TV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*'''1 April''' - 2 deaths reported in single day. First death in the state. One in [[Basti district|Basti]] and other in [[Meerut]].\n*'''3 April''' - 59 new cases reported in a single day out of which 54 are returned from [[2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|Tablighi Jamaat in Delhi]].\n\n==Response==\n\nOn 17 March, the [[Uttar Pradesh government]] extended the closure of all educational institutions, cinemas, shopping malls, swimming pool, gyms, mulitplexes and tourists places in the state till April 2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.businesstoday.in/lite/story/coronavirus-four-more-cases-reported-in-lucknow-up-total-now-at-23/1/398764.html|title=Coronavirus: Four more cases reported in Lucknow; UP total now at 23|website=m.businesstoday.in|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> [[District magistrate]]s were instructed to spread awareness through posters and banners on the viral disease. Additionally, an appeal was made to religious leaders to avoid crowding in temples, mosques, gurudwaras and churches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/corona-outbreak-uttar-pradesh-extends-shutdown-till-april-2/articleshow/74672722.cms|title=Corona outbreak: Uttar Pradesh extends 'shutdown' till April 2 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n[[Slaughterhouse]]s in state were ordered to be closed from 22 to 24 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livehindustan.com/uttar-pradesh/story-up-all-slaughterhouse-will-be-closed-from-22-to-24-march-due-to-coronavirus-3101485.html|title=\u0915\u094b\u0930\u094b\u0928\u093e : \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0930 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u092e\u0947\u0902 22 \u0938\u0947 24 \u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u091a \u0924\u0915 \u092c\u0902\u0926 \u0930\u0939\u0947\u0902\u0917\u0947 \u0938\u092d\u0940 \u0938\u094d\u0932\u0949\u091f\u0930 \u0939\u093e\u0909\u0938|website=www.livehindustan.com|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, Chief Minister [[Yogi Adityanath]] announced the lockdown of fifteen districts in state, from 22 to 25 March, including [[Noida]], [[Ghaziabad]], [[Agra]], [[Aligarh]], [[Prayagraj district|Prayagraj]], [[Kanpur]], [[Varanasi]], [[Bareilly]], Lucknow, [[Saharanpur]], [[Meerut]], [[Lakhimpur]], [[Azamgarh]], [[Gorakhpur]] and others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/india/story/coronavirus-live-updates-india-janata-curfew-world-news-italy-china-wuhan-france-covid-19-cases-1658331-2020-03-22|title=Coronavirus updates: Egypt senior military officer dies of Covid-19|date=22 March 2020|website=India Today|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCM [[Yogi Adityanath]] announced on 21 March that the Uttar Pradesh government has decided to give \u20b91,000 (US$14) to all daily wage laborers affected due to coronavirus in the state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/|title=Business News Live, Share Market News - Read Latest Finance News, IPO, Mutual Funds News|website=The Economic Times|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCM [[Yogi Adityanath]] dismissed District Magistrate of [[Gautam Buddh Nagar district]] BN Singh on 30 March 2020 and appointed Suhas L. Y. as New DM.\n\nOn 30th March, 2020, the migrant workers returning to [[Bareilly]] from [[Delhi]] were sprayed with disinfectant as a measure to curb the effects of coronavirus. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/north-and-central/migrant-workers-sprayed-with-disinfectant-in-uttar-pradesh-many-suffer-burning-sensation-819298.html|title=Migrant workers sprayed with 'disinfectant' in Uttar Pradesh; many suffer burning sensation|date=2020-03-30|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable citiwise-data\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:90%; width:100px;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |District\n! scope=\"col\" |Confirmed cases\n!Recovered\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n|-\n!Gorakhpur\n|1000\n|0\n|0<br />\n|-\n![[Gautam Buddh Nagar district|'''Gautam Buddh Nagar''']]\n|50\n|6\n|0\n|-\n![[Meerut district|'''Meerut''']]\n|25\n|0\n|'''1'''\n|-\n![[Agra district|'''Agra''']]\n|19\n|8\n|0\n|-\n![[Saharanpur district|Saharanpur]]\n|13\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Lucknow district|'''Lucknow''']]\n|10\n|1\n|0\n|-\n![[Ghaziabad district, Uttar Pradesh|'''Ghaziabad''']]\n|10\n|2\n|0\n|-\n![[Kanpur Nagar district|'''Kanpur''']]\n|7\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Bareilly district|Bareilly]]\n|6\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Shamli district|'''Shamli''']]\n|6\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Basti district|Basti]]\n|5\n|0\n|'''1'''\n|-\n![[Varanasi district|'''Varanasi''']]\n|5\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Azamgarh district|Azamgarh]]\n|4\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Firozabad district|Firozabad]]\n|4\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Bulandshahr district|Bulandshahr]]\n|3\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Jaunpur district|'''Jaunpur''']]\n|3\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Bagpat district|'''Baghpat''']]\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Pilibhit district|'''Pilibhit''']]\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Pratapgarh district, Uttar Pradesh|Pratapgarh]]\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Ghazipur district|Ghazipur]]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Hardoi district|Hardoi]]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Hapur district|Hapur]]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Lakhimpur Kheri district|'''Lakhimpur Kheri''']]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Moradabad district|'''Moradabad''']]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n![[Shahjahanpur district|Shahjahanpur]]\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Total (all districts)\n! scope=\"col\" |182\n!17\n!2\n|- class=\"sortbottom\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"4\" |<small>As of 3 April 2020</small><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/lucknow-city-coronavirus-positive-in-up-162-positivecases-reported-in-the-up-34-persons-had-attended-the-tablighi-jamaat-event-in-delhi-20161603.html|title=CoronaVirus Positive in UP : \u0924\u092c\u094d\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 54 \u0932\u094b\u0917\u094b\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e \u0938\u0902\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0923, \u0906\u0902\u0915\u0921\u093c\u093e 182 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u093e|website=Dainik Jagran|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|}<br />\n\n== Confirmed deaths ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+{{nowrap|Details for COVID-19 cases who died in Uttar Pradesh}}\n!Case order\n!Date of Death\n!Age\n!Gender\n!District\n!Hospital admitted to\n!Been to other country\n!Note\n!Source\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1 April\n|25\n|Male\n|[[Basti district|Basti]]\n|[[Baba Raghav Das Medical College|Baba Raghav Das Medical College,Gorakhpur]]\n|No\n|Problems in his liver and kidney and he died after around 17 hours\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/uttar-pradesh-basti-youth-72-yr-old-kin-of-meerut-patient-succumb-to-covid-19-6342817/|title=Uttar Pradesh: Basti youth, 72-yr-old kin of Meerut patient succumb to COVID-19|date=2020-04-02|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n|-\n|2\n|72\n|Male\n|[[Meerut district|Meerut]]\n